<I><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#cfcfcf">Ranger of Karana</I></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucasidy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casidy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/10/01 7:31:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Okay... What a bunch of BS.</span><hr size=1> Just to clue those of you in... that might be clueless on this particular issue...<br>
<br>
Several facts:<br>
<br>
1- Bard song without a drum is slower than a lvl 14 sow.<br>
<br>
2- Casidy found out the hard way that Bard song was broken, running through Nek woods on the way to Sol A to hunt... with her MM drum in hand... and *gasp she got hit, and stunned, and nearly killed?!?*... (normally I fly past the guards so fast, that half the time they don't even aggro... and this is the case normally above lvl 15 even with a normal drum, but particularly above lvl 20 with a MM drum...)<br>
<br>
3- Casidy was not the only bard to have this problem... and I can only imagine how bad it is for some of my bardic friends at higher levels... the ones, much like myself, that are not forced to beg... with the masses, for a spirit of the wolf.<br>
<br>
4- Again I say... What a bunch of BS... if you know its broken, then fix it dammit... its bad enough the stuff that We know is broken that the gods can't seem to confirm... (like the falling for 10,000 pts of damage...in BB... *shrugs*)... <br>
<br>
Maybe I should just go play another class while I wait... I don't relish the idea of getting a group killed cause I/They can't run as fast as I/we are used to out of a tight spot... <br>
<br>
/rant off. <p><br><b><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2 COLOR="#6699cc">
