<br>
And for reference, this is a HUGE nerf.  A level 20 bard with a normal drum and BADLY outrun a druid using Form of the Howler (lvl 54 spell).<br>
<br>
Guess I'll make sure poor Cobayn has a SoW for the week or so until they fix this. <p><BR><br><B><I>-Santerre.</I></B></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujzonn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jzonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/10/01 8:24:00 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://personal.bhm.bellsouth.net/bhm/r/p/rpo2/Jzonn_Icon.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Okay... What a bunch of BS.</span><hr size=1> Yeah, I would recommend playing another char for a bit.  I wouldn't be surprised if they make an emergency patch later this week to fix the issues.  I'm not expecting it, though.<br>
<br>
FWIW, while I know a Bards song is faster, I generally don't want to use it.  If you have a Bard or even a party member who lags, you'll spend a lot of time trying to keep the song on everyone.<br>
<br>
Case in point (and I know this is anecdotal), this past weekend, my guild did a mini raid on Kaesora to get some fangs from Xalgoz.  On the way over, one group (mine) had a Bard with the song that levs, invises, see invises, and gives a movement boost.  After zoning into the Swamp of No Hope, we didn't get 10 seconds in and the Bard starts having lag problems.  This continued for another minute or so (and we didn't get very far).  Finally, I tell the group I'll meet them at the zone to Field of Bone.  I lev up, apply wolf spirit, and run across the zone.  I wait another 3-4 minutes for the rest of the group to show up. <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#3A6EA5">Jzonn Stormwolf &lt;Final Destiny&gt;</B></FONT><BR>
